  <body>
    <main class="wrap">
      <div class="page-title">
        <div class="icon">≡</div>
        <div>Mbps ↔ MB/s Explained</div>
      </div>

      <p class="subtitle">
        <strong>Mbps</strong> = megabits per second (Internet speed). <strong>MB/s</strong> = megabytes per second (download / file speed).
        <br />
        Quick rule: <strong>1 Byte = 8 bits</strong> → <strong>MB/s ≈ Mbps ÷ 8</strong>.
      </p>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Mbps vs MB/s">
        <div class="tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Sections">
          <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-tab="converter">Converter</button>
          <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="formula">Formula</button>
          <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="table">Table</button>
          <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="examples">Examples</button>
          <button class="tab" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="faq">FAQ</button>
        </div>

        <div class="panel">
          <!-- Panel: Converter -->
          <div data-panel="converter" class="active">
            <div class="option-block">
              <div class="option-title">
                <h2>Interactive Converter (Mbps ↔ MB/s)</h2>
                <div class="hint">Pick a mode, then enter a value</div>
              </div>

              <div>
                <label class="radio-row">
                  <input type="radio" name="mode" value="mbps2mbs" checked />
                  <span><strong>Mbps → MB/s</strong> (internet speed to download speed)</span>
                </label>

                <label class="radio-row">
                  <input type="radio" name="mode" value="mbs2mbps" />
                  <span><strong>MB/s → Mbps</strong> (download speed to internet speed)</span>
                </label>

                <label class="radio-row">
                  <input type="radio" name="mode" value="both" />
                  <span><strong>Two-way</strong> (typing either field updates the other)</span>
                </label>

                <div style="height: 8px;"></div>

                <div class="note muted">
                  <strong>Heads up:</strong> Real downloads are often lower due to protocol overhead, Wi-Fi, server limits, etc.
                  This converter is the clean math conversion.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div style="height: 10px;"></div>

              <div class="row">
                <div class="field">
                  <label for="mbpsInput">Megabits per second (Mbps)</label>
                  <input
                    id="mbpsInput"
                    class="input"
                    type="number"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                    step="any"
                    placeholder="e.g. 100"
                  />
                </div>

                <div class="field">
                  <label for="mbsInput">Megabytes per second (MB/s)</label>
                  <input
                    id="mbsInput"
                    class="input"
                    type="number"
                    inputmode="decimal"
                    step="any"
                    placeholder="e.g. 12.5"
